This paper deals with one-shot fine-grained visual recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves meta-learning, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of an image generator, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the proposed MetaIRNet involves neural networks, which is a subfield of both machine learning and artificial intelligence. Finally, the experiments involve image classification benchmarks, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM).
